&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and experienced DevOps Engineer to join our team dedicated to autonomous driving technology. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in infrastructure automation, a passion for robust deployment pipelines, and a deep understanding of multi-platform environments (Linux and Windows). You will play a crucial role in ensuring the continuous integration, continuous delivery (CI/CD), and high availability of our autonomous driving software stack through seamless automation, rigorous security practices, and resilient system architecture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and oversee the installation and deployment of software across multiple operating systems, including Linux, Windows. Ensure compatibility and seamless integration on different platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure easy installation and upgrade process for end-users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain automated pipelines for continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) to ensure fast, secure, reliable, and repeatable deployments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and enforce security best practices for deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement high availability strategies in deployment environments to ensure continuous uptime and reliability, including load balancing, replication, and failover mechanisms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain comprehensive release documentation, deployment instructions, and security checklists to ensure repeatable, compliant processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
