&lt;p&gt;■&amp;nbsp; Respect Diversity&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission of the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and experienced Platform Engineer to own the CI/CD pipelines, build systems, cloud infrastructure, and software delivery processes for our Autonomous Through Infrastructure (ATI) solution.&amp;nbsp;This role is responsible for building and operating the internal platform that raises productivity across the entire engineering team, reliably supporting a C++/Go/Python autonomous driving stack across multi-architecture environments (x86_64 + ARM64/NVIDIA Jetson). You will work hands-on across a broad range of infrastructure domains — from developer toolchain and access management to AWS operations, release engineering, high-availability (HA) architecture, and developer experience (DevEx) improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and maintain CI/CD pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate development workflows and operate static analysis pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and optimize build systems for multi-language, multi-architecture (x86, ARM) projects including C++-based codebases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Software packaging (Linux packages, Docker images), release strategy, and deployment automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement HA architecture for failover and service continuity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate AWS cloud resources, manage IaC, and maintain self-hosted runners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network access control and developer account/permission management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize development environments and improve developer experience (DevEx)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor platform stability and manage operational metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
